Wayne Rooney believes Manchester United can hunt down rivals City and Chelsea at the top of the Barclays Premier League.

Rooney turned in a man of the match performance from central midfield at Old Trafford on Friday as United strolled past Newcastle 3-1 in the Barclays Premier League.

The United skipper scored two and made one from his new position and said afterwards: 'We've chased leads down before but we've lost leads as well, and a big number of points before, so anything can happen especially over the next week or two with all the games.

