United will be without Marouane Fellaini and Adnan Januzaj at Tottenham as both are unwell. It also seems unlikely that winger Angel di Maria will be fit after suffering a pelvis injury in training on Christmas Eve.

'He was injured in a warming up, ' said Van Gaa.

'It is not a heavy injury, but you don't take risks I think.

'It is to do with the way his pelvis attaches to his leg.'

Newcastle could have had an early penalty yesterday but were eventually sunk by two Rooney goals in the first half and a header from Robin van Persie early in the second half. Substitute Papa Cisse grabbed an 85th consolation from the penalty spot.

